title: Horsebreder guid
author: jonassn1
pages:
#- A guide to Horses§0
§0
§0-------------------§0
§0
§0Transcript of a old horsebreeder explanation§0
§0
§0___________________§0
§0
§0Written down by Jonassn1
#- So ye want to learn a bit about the horses, ye lad?§0
§0
§0A horse, is that four legged animal over there, e allows ye to travell great distances at a wimp, and without much strain on ye wee feet.
#- The men in e church tell me, the horse was made by the Light Bearer by fussing flesh to a skeleton, I don't know about that lad. But they like sugar and apples.§0
§0
§0They also eat wheat and hay, but if ye want them to roll around in the hay feed them golden
#- carrots or apples.§0
§0
§0Ye can find them in the plains and savannas, and they can be tamed, by feeding them and trying to ride them. But be carefull,  lad they throw you of, but carry on. It will only surrender to one who is more stuborn than that.
#-  A horse there is tamed can be ridden, but you will not control it without a saddle, they can also be corvered in armor, however they are not really usefull to fight on.§0
§0
§0A horse can be bred with e donkey, their ofspring is a mule, and it can carry quite 
#- a load.§0
§0
§0Oh a horse can run between 5 blocks a second and 14 seconds, but it depends on its breed.§0
§0
§0E hope that ye enlightned ye lad.
#- 